The paper deals with constraint satisfaction problems (CSPs), which are typically studied in the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and data structures (cs.DS) sub-categories. The paper also involves the study of patterns and their absence, which falls under the sub-categories of logic in computer science (cs.LO) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). Finally, the paper discusses the solvability of CSPs, which can be related to computational complexity (cs.CC).
